text: Fyter Fest (2020) was a two-part professional wrestling show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on July 1 and July 2, 2020 at Daily's Place in Jacksonville, Florida. It was aired on July 1 and July 8, since Night 2 was pre-recorded. Both nights aired as special episodes of Dynamite. It was the second Fyter Fest event held by AEW. The event was originally going to be the United Kingdom debut of AEW and was going to take place at Wembley Arena but it had the be cancelled because of the COVID-19 pandemic. Night 1's main event saw Kenny Omega and Adam Page defeat Best Friends (Chuck Taylor and Trent) to successfully retain their AEW World Tag Team Championships. Night 2's main event saw Chris Jericho defeat Orange Cassidy. The original main event of the show was going to see Brian Cage face Jon Moxley for Moxley's AEW World Championship.
